* a) Storage, under pressure of more than 0.1 N/mm<sup>2</sup> and in quantities exceeding 70 m<sup>3</sup> of acetylene, hydrogen, illuminating and natural gases, ammonia, chlorine, phosphene, sulphur dioxide, carbon dioxide, methyloxide and all gases subject to explosion, fume or toxic hazard, cryogenic gases, etc;

* b) Storage and handling of hazardous and flammable/toxic liquids and gases like LPG, rocket propellants, etc;

* c) Storage and handling of hazardous and highly flammable or explosive materials, other than liquids; and

* d) Manufacture of artificial flowers, synthetic leather, ammunition, explosives and fireworks.
